# Testing & Verification — {{PROJECT_NAME}}

The gate is **{{GATE}}** (+ a real-world check of the feature), not a number for its own sake. Be
pragmatic: test the rules that matter; verify the thing actually works.

## The suites
{{List the project's test layers and their commands, e.g.:}}
- **Unit** ({{UNIT_CMD}}) — pure logic; deterministic; no network.
- **Integration** ({{INT_CMD}}) — service/data-layer flows.
- **{{Other}}** ({{...}}) — {{e.g. row-security, e2e}}.
- **Gate** ({{GATE}}) — runs the above + type-check/build and reports PASS/FAIL.

## Real-world verification (don't ship on green tests alone)
{{How to actually exercise the change — e.g. drive the UI headless and screenshot, hit the API,
inspect output. Reading the result is part of "done".}}

## Definition of done
- Type-check + build clean.
- {{GATE}} all-PASS.
- The affected behaviour verified for real.
- Knowledge base updated (`.claude/database/database.md` + relevant `knowledgebase/<module>`) in the same change.

## Test data
Use deterministic seeded data ({{SEED_CMD}}); tests that mutate shared/cloud data must clean up.
